    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-03-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-03-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="388"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Williams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 25.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-03-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 6, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 23d of November last, No.
                    16, informing me of the reprint in Japan of Wheaton’s International Law, and the
                    beneficial results which may be expected from this proceeding, has been received
                    and read with great interest.</p>
                <p>The importance which you ascribe to the appointment of Seu-ki-yu to a post in the
                    Foreign Office seems to be well founded. It is gratifying to this government to
                    learn from these events that the efforts and purposes of the western powers are
                    appreciated, and it views them as proof of the advance in China of the
                    sentiments of western civilization.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">S. Wells Williams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
